FBIS4-21853 "jptot015__l94018" JPRS-TOT-94-015-L JPRS Terrorism FOUO 7 April 1994 LATIN AMERICA COLOMBIA Bomb Explodes in Northern Part of Capital; Damage Reported Bomb Explodes in Northern Part of Capital; Damage Reported PA0704171694 Santa Fe de Bogota Emisoras Caracol Network in Spanish 1200 GMT 7 Apr 94 PA0704171694 Santa Fe de Bogota Emisoras Caracol Network Spanish BFN [From "Caracol's 0600-0900" newscast] [Text] Santa Fe de Bogota -- A new explosion was reported a short while ago in the northern part of the capital of the Republic. A small explosive device detonated, causing damage in a three-story building near the intersection of 24th Avenue and 75th Street. The bomb was placed at the Electra Drugstore. Several nearby homes also sustained damage, which is being assessed at this time by police and the Santa Fe de Bogota Fire Department.
